                <head>No. 1103.<lb/>
                    <hi rend="italic">Mr. <persName type="from">Bayard</persName> to Mr. <persName
                            type="to">Straus</persName>.</hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Department of State</hi>,<lb/>
                            <hi rend="italic">Washington</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1888-11-21">
                            <hi rend="italic">November</hi> 21, 1888</date>.</dateline>
                    <seg rendition="#left">No. 159.]</seg>
                </opener>
                <p>
                    <hi rend="smallcaps">Sir</hi>: I have much satisfaction in acknowledging Mr.
                    King’s dispatch, No. 133, of the 3d instant, reporting that His Imperial Majesty
                    the Sultan had decided to grant an iradeh to the representatives of the
                    University of Pennsylvania permitting archaeological explorations in Assyria and
                    Babylonia.</p>
                <p>I am, etc.,</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">T. F. Bayard.</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
